            <string>Semi-Recommended cMIOS. A cMIOS with Swiss r1788 built-in. Hold Y during any GameCube mode load to start the built-in Swiss.  If Y is not held, then it should behave identically to WiiGator\WiiPower's cMIOS and official MIOS. While this is the ideal cMIOS, because of Nintendont, cMIOSs are generally not needed, unless loading backup Gamecube discs on older compatible Wiis.

                                                                              Based on MIOSv10.</string>
           </property>
          </item>
          <item>
           <property name="text">
            <string>WiiGator\Power cMIOS-v0.2 [10]</string>
           </property>
           <property name="toolTip">
            <string>Since Nintendont, cMIOSs are generally not needed, unless loading backup Gamecube discs on older compatible Wiis.

                                                                              Based on MIOSv10.</string>
           </property>
          </item>
          <item>
           <property name="text">
            <string>WiiGator cMIOS-v0.2 [4]</string>
           </property>
           <property name="toolTip">
            <string>Since Nintendont, cMIOSs are generally not needed, unless loading backup Gamecube discs on older compatible Wiis.

                                                                              Based on MIOSv4.</string>
           </property>
          </item>
          <item>
           <property name="text">
            <string>Waninkoko cMIOS-rev5 [4]</string>
           </property>
           <property name="toolTip">
            <string>Since Nintendont, cMIOSs are generally not needed, unless loading backup Gamecube discs on older compatible Wiis.

                                                                              Based on MIOSv4.</string>
           </property>
          </item>
          <item>
           <property name="text">
            <string>DIOS MIOS Lite (DML) v2.11</string>
           </property>
           <property name="toolTip">
            <string>Since Nintendont, DML is generally not used anymore.

                                                                              DML (Dios Mios Lite) is a tool which allows you to run Gamecube games from an SD Card.

                                                                              Note: for DML to work with SNEEK+DI the WAD must be installed to real NAND and accessed via an emulated NAND.

                                                                              Games must be in discex format, use discex or ModMii's Game Bulk Extractor.</string>
           </property>
          </item>
          <item>
           <property name="text">
            <string>DIOS MIOS v2.11</string>
           </property>
           <property name="toolTip">
